Kenyatta today led top government officials in receiving the covid-19 vaccine, hours after he directed all cabinet secretaries to get the jab. Top officials who included Acting Chief Justice Philomena Mwilu and cabinet secretaries led by health CS Mutahi Kagwe and his interior counterpart Fred Matiang&rsquo;i also took the jab at state house, Nairobi, in a move geared to persuade kenyans to get vaccinated, amid recent doubts on the safety of the Oxford Astrazeneca vaccine that have fueled nationwide hesitancy.